in the 4th district runoff tuesday, brookhaven funeral home director mike parker, a 38-year-old political newcomer, defeated brad pigott, a 33-year-old jackson attorney, in the democratic runoff. thomas collins iii defeated andy taggart on the republican side. collins is executive director of the mississippi veterans home purchase board. taggart is a jackson attorney
in the 5th district, state sen. gene taylor of bay st. louis defeated glenn white of hattiesburg, while 43-year-old sheriff larkin smith of gulfport outdistanced hattiesburg businessman george robert hall, 57, in the republican runoff
in a runoff race for the democratic nomination for a vacant seat on the state supreme court, former attorney general ed pittman defeated laurel attorney jon swartzfager by a 3-to-2 margin
the races were left over from contests on super tuesday
two buses loaded with teen-agers returning from a visit to the nation's capital collided on a bridge that crosses san francisco bay, injuring at least 20 people and closing the span for more than two hours
the accident tuesday night began when a car with a flat tire stopped in the fast lane of the 9{-mile-long san mateo bridge, said california highway patrol investigator nick chouprov
the buses carried 72 youngsters from modesto junior high schools. the first stopped and was struck from behind by the second, according to chouprov
the youngsters suffered only minor injuries, according to thomas mcgarry, a spokesman for eden hospital in castro valley
the most seriously injured was bus driver charles ford, 60, of oakland who was in serious condition with stomach injuries, he said. ``it took 20 minutes to get him out of the bus,'' mcgarry said
the driver of the car that stopped for the flat, xiaoyun zhou, 38, of hayward, was in serious condition with head injuries
the teen-agers from la loma and roosevelt junior high schools were en route home from san francisco international airport, where they had returned from a field trip to washington d.c
when we crashed into the other bus everybody started screaming and crying. the driver swerved but he still hit the bus,'' said kristi new, 13, of roosevelt
callie stewart, 13, also of roosevelt, said she flipped over a seat during the accident
i was sitting up and talking to my friend when i did a total flip,'' she said. ``everybody was screaming. after the bus stopped, people started hugging each other and asking if they were ok.''
some of the youngsters said police officers and paramedics got them out through the windows of the vehicles
three students who suffered minor injuries were treated and released at eden, said mcgarry. the most seriously injured was todd johnson, 12, who had a fractured arm
st. rose hospital treated seven youngsters, including two students with minor nose injuries, said spokeswoman debbie bartling. ten other students were treated at hospitals for minor injuries, mcgarry said
