it was ms. tabor's class at washington elementary school in merrill that initiated the drive last year to give the cranberry muffin official status
the proposal was still pending when assembly speaker thomas loftus decided to adjourn the democratic-controlled assembly late friday night before the senate could finish work o the 1988-89 state budget
loftus said his action was in part because the senate was spending its time discussing whether the cranberry muffin should be the state's official muffin
they (the senate) sent us the cranberry muffin bill at 11:30 p.m. and i think we snapped,'' loftus said
