the kuwaiti defense ministry said kuwaiti forces clashed today with three iranian gunboats that had opened fire on kuwait's bubiyan island in the northern end of the persian gulf. two kuwaiti soldiers were wounded
and iran said its warplanes dropped 10 tons of bombs on an northern iraqi provincial capital. and iraq said it fired three long-range missiles into the central iranian city of isfahan, ancient capital of the persian empire
