the anax, which was also hit by iraqi warplanes dec. 2, was attacked south of iran's big kharg island oil terminal in the northern gulf with a full load of oil. it was on charter to the national iranian tanker co
both sides have resumed the ``tanker war'' in the last two weeks, hitting about a dozen vessels. two iranian tankers were set ablaze in an iraqi air raid on kharg march 19, killing at least 50 seamen
nearly 500 ships have been attacked by both sides since 1981 and nearly 300 seamen killed
in other action today, tehran radio, monitored in nicosia, reported that a squadron of iranian fighter-bombers attacked three ``important military garrisons'' in sulaimaniyeh city, an iraqi provincial capital in the northeastern mountains
the communique said dozens of people were killed in the attacks, in which the regional state-run radio and television headquarters was also hit. it was one of the heaviest bombing raids by iran's badly depleted air force reported in a year
iran said it was launched in retaliation for iraqi chemical bomb attacks on three kurdish towns in the northeast march 16-17 in which tehran claims 5,000 civilians were killed and 5,000 injured
the towns had been captured by iranian revolutionary guards, who have pushed 15 miles into kurdistan, where ethnic kurds have been in rebellion against baghdad
the iranians claim to have seized 540 square miles of iraqi territory in the two-week old offensive. iraq has admitted losing ground, but given no details
the kuwait news agency reported two kuwait soldiers were wounded today in a skirmish initiated by iranian gunboats at bubiyan island, 15 miles south of iraq's coast. it did not say if the iranian vessels were struck
