detroit _ her school principal had urged her mother to make the four-hour drive from rural northern michigan. now 11-year-old chrissie sat in a windowless office where a psychologist peppered her with questions. the morning would end with doctors at the attention deficit disorder clinic of children's hospital telling chrissie her baffling problems at home and in school would mean treatment with the stimulant ritalin
