ivana trump has a chance at some hot tips on how to run a big-time hotel offered by the owner of a boarding house in a town with a population of 361 people
the wife of new york real estate magnate donald trump has been invited to drop down and pick up some of the finer points of the hospitality trade at mary bobo's boarding house
the boarding house, which opened in 1908 in this rural community, is known for its southern hospitality and tennessee food served in a wooden building surrounded by a white picket fence
lynne tolley, proprietress of the boarding house, made the invitation in a letter tuesday to mrs. trump after learning that she will run new york city's plaza hotel, which her husband recently purchased for $390 million
mrs. tolley didn't say whether she would give mrs. trump tips on how to negotiate a salary. at the time of the plaza purchase, trump announced his wife would work for $1 and all the dresses she can buy
welcome to atlanta. if you are going down the escalator, you will be entering the transportation mall ...''
millions of travelers each year hear the message at hartsfield atlanta international airport, and the woman whose voice is behind the words says they've given new meaning to her life
lee mcallister's taped announcement began running when the new midfield terminal opened in 1980. ``people immediately wanted to know who the voice was, and i made sure word got around,'' she said
she now has more than 1,800 radio and tv commercials to her credit and is always a hit at parties. ``people are always saying, `do the airport voice, lee, do the airport voice,''' she said
airport officials hired ms. mcallister because ``we needed someone who could guide people through the airport, whose voice was calm, collected and soothing,'' said j.r. mcintyre of the atlanta airlines terminal corp. ``it's kind of like the cowboys who sang to the herds.''
