four-pound, 1{-ounce calvin williams was born tuesday seven weeks premature as his mother, dina williams, 29, of lorain, was being rushed from amherst hospital to metro general, which has a neonatal intensive care unit
when the staff at amherst realized mrs. williams was in labor, they contacted metro general for a life flight helicopter, said metro general spokesman george stamatis. the helicopter, carrying two pilots, a nurse and a doctor, arrived at amherst within a half-hour, and soon after that, it was aloft again with mrs. williams
