the charges were investigated by the poughkeepsie police, who determined that they were unfounded and apparently fabricated to cover up sexual abuse by a male relative, the news said
the rev. al sharpton, an adviser to the brawley family, angrily denounced the news story, and he and one of the brawleys' attorneys, alton maddox, asserted that it had been leaked by state attorney general robert abrams, the special prosecutor in the case
it's ridiculous to take a story that no one has established that tawana had any knowledge of and imply that she was trying to use it,'' sharpton said
a spokesman for abrams, timothy gilles, declined to comment on the reports, but denied that abrams' office had been the source of the story
the case has received wide attention, in part because the family has refused to cooperate with officials, accusing them of racial bias in their handling of the investigation
