four days later she was found near her family's former apartment in wappingers falls, dazed, covered with animal excrement and with racial epithets written on her body. miss brawley is black
a state-owned magazine says a ranking libyan visited egypt in an attempt to mend relations between the north african neighbors, which have been at odds for years and fought a brief border war in 1977
in the edition appearing thursday, the weekly al-mussawar said col. abdel-fattah younis farag came to cairo after egypt allowed the return of four libyan warplanes whose pilots landed on the wrong side of the border march 1 because of bad weather and lack of fuel
on monday, libyan leader moammar gadhafi said he was withdrawing his forces from the border and asked nothing in return. he said libya would not use force to get president hosni mubarak's government to renounce the peace treaty egypt signed with israel in 1979
mubarak reacted to that gesture wednesday by warning gadhafi not to conceal terrorist plans behind expressions of good will
