wheat futures opened slightly higher but other grain and soybean futures opened a little lower today on the chicago board of trade
wheat got a boost from news this morning that the soviet union will bid thursday for 500,000 metric tons of u.s. wheat, analysts said
acceptance of the bid by the agriculture department would complete a soviet purchase of 1 million metric tons of wheat recently offered under the usda's export enhancement program
but the u.s. is likely to offer the soviets another million metic tons of subsidized wheat in the near future, said richard loewy, senior grain and oilseed analyst for prudential-bache securities inc
