wheat was supported by expectations that the soviet union would bid thursday for 500,000 metric tons of u.s. wheat, analysts said. acceptance of the bid by the usda would complete a soviet purchase of 1 million metric tons of wheat it was recently offered under the usda's export enhancement program
the slight downward movement of soybeans and the other grains reflected position-evening ahead of the usda's thursday afternoon reports on spring planting intentions and u.s. grain stocks, said joel karlin, research analyst for research department inc. in chicago
