texaco inc. said it filed an appeal of a multibillion-dollar damage judgment to the u.s. supreme court on wednesday, but stressed the move was only a formality in the event its settlement with pennzoil co. fell through
texaco agreed in december to pay pennzoil $3 billion in return for pennzoil dropping the $10.3 billion judgment. the settlement was the keystone of a bankruptcy reorganization plan that was approved by a u.s. bankruptcy court judge in white plains, n.y., last week
the plan is scheduled to take effect april 7, at which time texaco is to transfer $3 billion to pennzoil and begin payment of $2.6 billion to its other creditors. texaco said it would withdraw its request for a supreme court hearing at that time
pennzoil won the judgment when a houston jury ruled texaco had improperly interfered with a pennzoil acquisition of part of getty oil co. and bought all of getty itself
texaco filed for bankruptcy court protection last april to avoid having to pay a $11 billion security bond while appealing that judgment
turner broadcasting system inc. said wednesday its fourth-quarter loss narrowed to $27.2 million in 1987 from $65.9 million a year earlier as its revenue rose 23.9 percent
the broadcasting and sports company said revenue for the quarter ended dec. 31 rose to $193.1 million from $155.9 million a year earlier
operating income for the quarter more than doubled to $64.9 million from $27.4 million for the same quarter the previous year
the company said fourth quarter earnings included a charge of $13.1 million to reduce the value of certain internally produced programming to its estimated net realizable value. the earnings also included a $10 million credit resulting from recognition of copyright fee income which had been the subject of litigation
for the year ended dec. 31, the company lost $131.2 million on revenue of $652.4 million, compared to a net loss of $187.3 million on revenue of $556.9 million for 1986
operating income for the year climbed 69 percent to $217.4 million from $128.4 million a year earlier
